# benches/oracles/bbolt/VERSIONS
#
# Pinned bbolt oracle version. This is the source of truth for the
# go.mod in this directory and for supply-chain review. Shell-
# sourceable (KEY=VALUE, no quotes needed).
#
# The bbolt pin is chosen to track etcd's stable-line usage (etcd
# v3.5.x ships bbolt v1.3.x). The exact go.mod pin and go.sum
# integrity checksums are checked in alongside this file; verify by
# running `go mod verify` in this directory.
#
# Why TOFU-per-go.sum rather than a separate sha256: `go mod verify`
# uses Go's checksum database (sum.golang.org) plus go.sum's
# h1: hash. go.sum is committed, which gives reproducible builds
# without a second manual sha channel. See README.md `## Threat
# model`.
#
# To bump: update BBOLT_VERSION here, run `go get
# go.etcd.io/bbolt@<NEW>` in this directory, then `go mod tidy`,
# then `go mod verify`, then commit the resulting go.mod/go.sum
# diff. CI will refuse to merge if go.sum is out of sync.

BBOLT_VERSION=v1.3.11
